   <text:p text:style-name="P55"><text:a xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#noteref.2.370.2" text:style-name="Internet_20_link" text:visited-style-name="Visited_20_Internet_20_Link"><text:span text:style-name="Definition">33</text:span></text:a>Â <text:span text:style-name="T1">Illic qui Serapin colunt, christiani suntÂ ; et devoti sunt Serapi, qui se Christi episcopos dicunt. Nemo illic archisynagogus judÅrum, nemo samarites, nemo christianorum presbyter, non mathematicus, non aruspex, non aliptes, qui non Serapin colat. Ipse ille patriarcha (judÅorum scilicet) cum AEgyptum venerit. ab aliis Serapin adorare, ab aliis cogitur Christum. Unus illis deus est SÃ©rapisÂ : hunc judÅi, hunc christiani, hunc omnes venerantur et gentes.</text:span> Flavius Vopiscus, <text:span text:style-name="T1">in Vita Saturnini.</text:span> Vid. <text:span text:style-name="T1">HistoriÅ augustÃ¦ scriptores,</text:span> in-fol., 1620, p. 245Â ; et in-8Âº, 1661, t. II, p. 719. (M.)</text:p>
